Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.96,0:00:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As we've seen with the Snowy Owl, all living things compete for the resources they need
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.58,0:00:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive and reproduce.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.09,0:00:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's much more to reproduction than just having enough energy to produce offspring
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to attract a mate
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.82,0:00:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,One way of doing is to show off.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.54,0:00:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A very good example of that is the peacock's tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.05,0:00:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Peahens prefer peacocks with flamboyant tails with plenty of eye spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.44,0:00:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so over time, the peacock's tail has become more and more extravagant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.66,0:00:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what's known as sexual selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.45,0:00:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In comparison with the peacock, the peahen is drab.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.04,0:00:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an advantage to her when she's sitting on her nest keeping her eggs warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.05,0:00:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So over countless generations, the effects of sexual selection and natural selection
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.45,0:00:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,have exaggerated the difference between males and females.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.61,0:01:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Between peacocks and peahens.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.22,0:01:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,
